<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1654,2041]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1654,1680]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Acrostichal setulae in 2 rows (
<figureCitation box="[622,712,1654,1681]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). A pair of processes on male abdominal sternite VI shorter than 
<quantity box="[151,239,1690,1717]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
, proximally parallel, distally divergent (
<figureCitation box="[689,774,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 9P</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1654,2041]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,526,1726,1752]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Supplementary description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[961,1141,1726,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xenalocasiae">
<emphasis box="[961,980,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[995,1141,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">xenalocasiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 3–5 per side. Eye with fine, sparse interfacetal setulae. Cibarial, medial sensilla 2–3 per side; posterior sensilla 1–2 per side. Supralateral seta outside prementum 1 per side. Prescutellar acrostichal setae absent (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1278,1798,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,920,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-75@10.[151,1435,919,1851]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Characters 7‒11 on the thorax (A‒D, dorsal view; E‒G, lateral view) of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, E), C. grandis sp. nov. (B), C. cristata de Meijere (C, F), C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (D) and C. ecornuta sp. nov. (G). Abbreviations: a dc s, anterior dorsocentral setae; ap sctl s, apical scutellar seta; b sctl s, basal scutellar seta; p kepst s, posterior katepisternal seta; pprn s, postpronotal seta; trn sut, transverse suture. Scale bars: 0.5 mm in A‒D, 0.1 mm in E‒G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766412" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766412/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Costal setae in middle row all weak, trichoid. Mid tibia with approximately 2 apical, stout setae. Male abdominal sternite III longer than wide, rectangular; IV as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[720,825,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[151,1435,181,1511]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 27A</figureCitation>
). Epandrium pubescent except for anterior margin and anteroventral elongation, posteroventrally less extended, with 13–14 setae on ventral portion of each side (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[151,1435,181,1511]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
). Surstylus long, distally tapering, apically truncate plate with 3 recurved teeth apically and 1 minute seta subapically (
<figureCitation box="[295,400,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[151,1435,181,1511]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
). Cercus pubescent except for anterior margin and ventral 1/4 (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1223,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[151,1435,181,1511]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
). Oviscapt about 4 times as long as wide, with 11–14 ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[673,773,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-22@42.[151,1435,181,1511]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda &amp; Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 27F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5766460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" startId="42.[151,250,1535,1559]" targetBox="[151,1435,181,1510]" targetPageId="42">
